Leapfrog2 - Dynamic mapping of Early farming

T. Huet

7/22/2020

Presentation of ‘Leapfrog2’ app

The structure of the leapfrog2 app was created in the framework of the french ANR CIMO project, under the direction of Didier Binder (CEPAM-CNRS).

The app first version (leapfrog) is a standalone one which simulate a GIS interface to facilitate the updating of a worksheet grouping data on first farming sites across Italy and Southern France. At the present time this important dataset is under revision. Therefore, I have adapted the structure of the RShiny app to read my own data. These latter are only here as a training set.

leapfrog2 URL is https://epispat.shinyapps.io/leapfrog2/

Window ‘map’

This first window need to be refresh by moving the chronological slider.

The upper part of the window shows a OSM basemap handle in RShiny by leaflet, the bottom part of the window show the listing of the features which appear on the map (the others are hided)

To get information on a feature, click on this feature.

To get a lat / long position on the map, clik on the position. OSM map give precious and precise information on the geographical situation of various ‘important’ places, caves, shelter, etc.

The Actualise button is only working in the standalone app (actualy leapfrog) .

Window ‘data’

The second windows present the whole dataset with various search and order tools.
